    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="640"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/264</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by Mr. David Williamson of the Division of Western
                        European Affairs</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-15">November 15,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Micheli called today to say that he had been advised that a Swiss textile
                    expert was about to proceed to the United States to investigate <pb facs="0848"
                        n="772" xml:id="pg_772"/> the effect of the proposed concessions on Swiss
                    textile exports. He inquired whether we had any objection.</p>
                <p>In reply he was told that we would not refuse to receive the expert if the Swiss
                    Government wished to send him as an official delegate. On the other hand, we see
                    no reason for sending such an expert. The delay caused by this trip seemed
                    inexcusable. Mr. Micheli was reminded of our attitude which is that we are not
                    prepared to grant any more concessions, but are waiting for his Government’s
                    reply to our requests.</p>
                <p>Mr. Micheli said he agreed that the expert’s trip was unnecessary, and was going
                    to so telegraph Mr. Stucki.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D[<hi rend="smallcaps">avid</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >illiamson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
